* What is a server
   * A piece of hardware or software that provides functionality to clients.  client server model.
   Provide various functionality like sharing data or performing computation for a client.   A single
   server can serve multiple clients, and a single client can use multiple servers.
   * A web server is a software that delivers web pages. A server is an actual computer.
* What is the role of the domain name
   * Domain names serve to identify Internet resources, such as computers, networks, and services, with a
    text-based label that is easier to memorize than the numerical addresses used in the Internet protocols.
* What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
   * The use of www.website.com gives you the opportunity to use a CNAME for www that points to your CDN,
    while leaving the required NS and SOA records on website.com. The website.com record will usually also
	have an A record to point to a host that will redirect to www.website.com using an HTTP redirect.
* What is the role of the web server
   * On the hardware side, a web server is a computer that stores web server software and a website's component
    files (e.g. HTML documents, images, CSS stylesheets, and JavaScript files). It is connected to the Internet
	and supports physical data interchange with other devices connected to the web.
   * On the software side, a web server includes several parts that control how web users access hosted files,
   at minimum an HTTP server. An HTTP server is a piece of software that understands URLs (web addresses) and
   HTTP (the protocol your browser uses to view webpages). It can be accessed through the domain names
   * webserver satisfies the client request on the world wide web
* What is the role of the application server
   * Just a server specifically designed to run applications such as webapps, data processing, software distribution.
* What is the role of the database
   * Holds all permanent data about the website, to be more specific depends on the site, twitter holds users tweets etc, our airbnb had a database to hold many things like reviews users, locations etc.
* What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
   * Depends which server: the web server uses TCP/IP.
Issues
* You must be able to explain what the issues are with this infrastructure:
   * Single point of failure
   * Downtime when maintenance needed (like deploying new code web server needs to be restarted)
   * Cannot scale for traffic
